data.chText: （英国）爵士头衔，骑士头衔，爵士称号，骑士称号
data.enText: (in Britain) the rank or title of a knight

data.chText: 他是新年受勋者之一，荣获爵士称号。
data.enText: He received a knighthood in the New Year's Honours list.

word_means: 爵士头衔，骑士头衔，爵士称号，骑士称号

means: (英国)爵士头衔，骑士头衔，爵士称号，骑士称号

tr: aristocrats holding the rank of knight

value.def: A knighthood is a title that is given to a man by a British king or queen for his achievements or his service to his country. A man who has been given a knighthood can put 'Sir' in front of his name instead of 'Mr'.
value.tran: （英国国王或女王授予的）爵士头衔，骑士头衔，爵士称号，骑士称号（其名前冠以Sir）
